<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<P>The Time Warner Cable Group announced a policy that programming found to be "indecent" would be made available only to customers who request it in writing. In this memorandum supporting a motion for an injunction, Al Goldstein, the producer of Midnight Blue and other sexually-oriented programs, argues that the cable company is attempting to restrict his First Amendment rights. Joining him in the action are Robin Byrd, host of a show that features strippers, and the Gay Cable Network.</P>



<P>EDITOR'S NOTE: The parent company of Time Warner Cable, Time Warner Inc., is a part owner of Court TV.</P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>

