74  S  v  J  1989 (1) SA 669 (A) at 682G. "Generally speaking,
however, retribution has tended to yield ground to the aspects
of  correction and prevention, and it is deterrence (including
prevention) which has been described as the 'essential',  'all
important', 'paramount' and 'universally admitted'  object  of
punishment".  Id. at 682I-J (cited with approval in S v P 1991
(1)  SA 517 (A) at 523G-H).  Cf. R v Swanepoel 1945 AD 444  at
453-455.

